{"proposal":{"id":"373","messages":[],"status":"PROPOSAL_STATUS_PASSED","final_tally_result":{"yes_count":"18358100313435","abstain_count":"1659491216540","no_count":"115000000","no_with_veto_count":"0"},"submit_time":"2026-03-18T23:50:29.583756156Z","deposit_end_time":"2026-03-28T23:50:29.583756156Z","total_deposit":[{"denom":"ujuno","amount":"5000000000"}],"voting_start_time":"2026-03-19T00:08:59.494057187Z","voting_end_time":"2026-03-24T00:08:59.494057187Z","metadata":"https://hackmd.io/s/HyZu6qv5Zl","title":"JunoClaw — Verifiable AI Agents with TEE-Attested Junoswap Revival on Juno","summary":"JunoClaw is an open-source agentic AI platform built natively on Juno Network. This signaling proposal asks the community to recognize JunoClaw as Juno ecosystem infrastructure and endorse the deployment of its contracts on mainnet as an experiment.\n\n\"Who knows, AI might actually be able to get JunoSwap working.\" — Jake Hartnell, Juno Telegram, March 18 2026\n\nThis proposal does not execute code. This proposal does not request community pool funds.\n\nFull proposal with all technical details, contract addresses, and links:\nhttps://hackmd.io/s/HyZu6qv5Zl\n\nWHAT EXISTS TODAY (Proven on uni-7 Testnet)\n\n- agent-company v3 contract live (code ID 63, 5 governance proposals executed)\n- Junoswap v2 factory and 2 trading pairs deployed (JUNOX/USDC, JUNOX/STAKE)\n- TEE hardware attestation proven (Intel SGX on Azure DCsv3)\n- WAVS operator stack LIVE on Akash decentralized compute (4 containers, ~US$8.76/month)\n- CodeUpgrade governance with 67% supermajority quorum\n- On-chain randomness via NOIS/drand for sortition\n- 34 unit tests passing\n\nTHREE INTEGRATIONS\n\n1. JUNOSWAP FOR AGENTS: Clean rewrite from scratch. Two contracts, Apache 2.0. Factory + XYK AMM pair. Every swap triggers WAVS verification.\n\n2. WAVS TEE INTEGRATION: 494KB WASI component proven inside Intel SGX enclave. TX: 6EA1AE79D373BE7E57A8492A089E543ADA40B30CB5F7E69B177E607879D26B22 (uni-7).\n\n3. AKASH DECENTRALIZED INFRASTRUCTURE: Operator coordination on Akash Network. 4 containers, zero cloud dependency.\n\nGOVERNANCE: Genesis → 13 Buds\n\n- Genesis distributes weight to 13 DAO members\n- Normal proposals: 51% quorum (7 of 13)\n- Code upgrades: 67% supermajority (9 of 13)\n- Genesis loses voting power after budding\n\nWHAT WE ASK\n\n1. Recognize JunoClaw as Juno ecosystem infrastructure\n2. Support the Junoswap revival through verifiable agent verification\n3. Endorse Akash as the decentralized coordination layer\n4. Acknowledge the CodeUpgrade governance framework\n5. Support the validator sidecar proposal for distributed TEE attestation\n\nRISKS: Not audited. Testnet only. Solo developer. Experimental. Full risk disclosure at HackMD link above.\n\nLINKS\n- Code: https://github.com/Dragonmonk111/junoclaw\n- HackMD: https://hackmd.io/s/HyZu6qv5Zl\n- Agent-company (uni-7): juno1k8dxll425mcclacaxhrmkx9w5pznx9w5ggmw53tpj0c009ngfnjstj85k6\n- Junoswap Factory (uni-7): juno12v0t60msclf3hcj56clrnh575ct35clglqunr489aj0xsvawghvq3wtkkh\n\nProposed by VairagyaNodes — Juno staker since December 30, 2021. Validator candidate (unbonded, position 6).","proposer":"juno1qh8rgkdm77wrhlf7un20gz9gmtpxkyaeldt0pg","expedited":false,"failed_reason":""}}
